SIMPLE: energize
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Energize
<hw>En"er*gize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Energized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Energizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[From
<er>Energy</er>.]</ety> <def>To use strength in action; to act or
operate with force or vigor; to act in producing an effect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Of all men it is true that they feel and <qex>energize</qex>
first, they reflect and judge afterwards.</q> <rj><qau>J. C.
Shairp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Energize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Energize
<hw>En"er*gize</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To give strength or force to;
to make active; to alacrify; <as>as, to <ex>energize</ex> the
will</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Energizer</ent>⟦br⟧
